{
  "text": "[17] Assuming a 500 m thick AAIW layer, and using the upper range zonal mean currents, we obtain the following transports (in 10 6 m 3 s \u00c01 or Sv): \u00c05.2 \u00b1 0.6 Sv (SEIC), 6.0 \u00b1 0.6 Sv (SICC), \u00c04.3 \u00b1 0.9 Sv (EIC), 6.4 \u00b1 1.1 Sv (NICC) and \u00c02.8 \u00b1 0.6 Sv (NEIC), comparable with [CITATION_1] estimates at 35\u00b0W (ADCP section).",
  "correct_citation": {
